The Board of Trustees (BoT) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has constituted a committee to douse tension generated by the emergence of Ndudi Elumelu as the Minority Leader of the House of Representatives. Addressing newsmen, yesterday in Abuja, BoT Chairman Senator Walid Jibrin said the committee, headed by Senator Iorchia Ayu, had the mandate to submit its report to the BoT and NWC within one week. He stressed that the BoT “which is the conscience of the party” would always work in harmony with the National Working Committee (NWC), cooperate and consult with them to avoid taking conflicting positions. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE “We have decided to wade into the fracas in the House of Representatives as regards the minority leadership. To that effect, a committee has been formed under the chairmanship of Chief Senator Iyorchia Ayu, Senator David Mark, Senator Ibrahim Mantu, Senator Adolphus Wabara and Hon. Austin Opara as secretary of the committee. “They have been given a week to submit their report to the BoT and National Working Committee (and) thereafter, a decision would be taken. “So, I call on all our members to be law abiding and to ensure that our party keeps moving and to play the role of opposition. We have to be very careful and obey the party because the party is supreme. We congratulate the new leadership of the Senate for coming out with the leaders and the minority leaders,” he said. PDP BoT constitutes peace panel over House of Reps crisis House leadership: PDP summons Elumelu, Oke, Ikpeazu, others …PDP NWC summons Elumelu, Oke, Ikpeazu, others Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin